'''David John Blackman''' is a [[United Kingdom|British]] archaeologist specialising in [[ancient maritime history]]. He was a founder of the [[Nautical Archaeology Society|Committee for Nautical Archaeology]] in 1964,<ref name="bio - Oxford Archaeology">{{cite web|title=Dr David Blackman|url=http://www.arch.ox.ac.uk/DB1.html|publisher=University of Oxford|accessdate=11 March 2013}}</ref> and was its Chair from 1975 to 1976. He served as Director of the [[British School at Athens]] between 1996 and 2002.<ref>{{cite web|title=NAS Vice Presidents - David Blackman|url=http://www.nauticalarchaeologysociety.org/about/staff.php|work=Who are we?|accessdate=11 March 2013}}</ref> He is currently a [[Research fellow|Senior Research Fellow]] at the Centre for the Study of Ancient Documents, [[University of Oxford]].<ref name="bio - Oxford Archaeology" />

