[[File:Kondura,_Nin.2.jpg|thumb|right|300px|Condura replica]] '''Kondura''' or '''Condura''' ({{lang-el|Condoira}}{{citation needed|date=September 2018}}) was a type of ship used on the eastern shores of the Adriatic. It is first mentioned and described in the 10th century as part of the medieval [[Kingdom of Croatia (925–1102)|Croatia]]n navy. It is also mentioned in the 14th century as a type of ship used by the [[Republic of Ragusa]].<ref name="KahaneKahane1979">{{cite book|author1=Henry Romanos Kahane|author2=Renée Kahane|title=Graeca Et Romanica Scripta Selecta: Romance and Mediterranean lexicology|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=miskAAAAMAAJ|year=1979|publisher=Hakkert}}</ref> The condura was {{convert|7|to|8|m|ft}} long.<ref>{{cite book|title=Byzantinoslavica|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=kw4rAQAAIAAJ|year=2007|publisher=Academia}}</ref>
==Condura croatica== In 1966, remains of two ships were accidentally found by the port of [[Nin, Croatia|Nin]], which, in 1974, were taken out and transferred to [[Zadar]] to restore and conserve the remains. Through [[radiocarbon dating]], it was established that these ships sailed from the end of 11th century to the start of 12th century. ==References== {{reflist}} ==External links== *http://www.enciklopedija.hr/natuknica.aspx?id=32756
